title: Google\Cloud\DataCatalog\V1\SearchCatalogResult
name: SearchCatalogResult
description:
A result that appears in the response of a search request. Each result captures details of one entry that matches the search.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.datacatalog.v1.SearchCatalogResult

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.search_result_type
params.description: Type of the search result. This field can be used to determine which Get method to call to fetch the full resource.

params.name: data.search_result_subtype
params.description: Sub-type of the search result. This is a dot-delimited description of the resource's full type, and is the same as the value callers would provide in the "type" search facet. Examples: entry.table, entry.dataStream, tagTemplate.

params.name: data.relative_resource_name
params.description: The relative resource name of the resource in URL format. Examples: projects/{project_id}/locations/{location_id}/entryGroups/{entry_group_id}/entries/{entry_id} projects/{project_id}/tagTemplates/{tag_template_id}

params.name: data.linked_resource
params.description: The full name of the cloud resource the entry belongs to. See: https://cloud.google.com/apis/design/resource_names#full_resource_name. Example: * //bigquery.googleapis.com/projects/projectId/datasets/datasetId/tables/tableId

params.name: data.integrated_system
params.description: Output only. This field indicates the entry's source system that Data Catalog integrates with, such as BigQuery or Cloud Pub/Sub.

params.name: data.user_specified_system
params.description: This field indicates the entry's source system that Data Catalog does not integrate with.
